
	Tutorial
1. Change directory to demo-backup 
2. Execute index.sh 

Note: 
-Before executing, please config hosts file (/etc/hosts) and restart network service. 
	- add ip address of backup server to /etc/hosts 
		folowing this syntax:  <ip address> server-backup

- To schedule local backup you need to create SSH-Keygen between server and client
	●	Create SSH key 
			ssh-keygen
	●	Create SSH without password
			ssh-copy-id hostname
	or folow this tutorial: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-configure-ssh-key-based-authentication-on-a-linux-server
-  To prepare for backuping to ggdrive, read this instruction: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-configure-ssh-key-based-authentication-on-a-linux-server